I feel so alone.

6
00:00:23,180 --> 00:00:25,670
Please, won't you stay with me?

7
00:00:27,080 --> 00:00:28,320
Shiori.

8
00:00:29,780 --> 00:00:31,300
Jiro-kun.

9
00:00:32,500 --> 00:00:35,660
Yakuin? Yakuin?

10
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:38,420
Yakuin!

11
00:00:41,200 --> 00:00:43,800
Damn it. It turned out to be a dream again.

12
00:00:43,800 --> 00:00:46,860
Come on, hurry up! I know you're awake, Yakuin!

13
00:00:48,250 --> 00:00:50,740
I can't go through this every single...

14
00:00:52,120 --> 00:00:54,980
Just for tonight... stay with me.

15
00:00:56,660 --> 00:00:57,490
Huh?

16
00:00:58,880 --> 00:01:04,750
What percentage does "like" have to hit before you can call it "love"?

17
00:01:13,960 --> 00:01:15,860
It's criminal to be so shy

18
00:01:15,860 --> 00:01:19,720
Intelligence and wild fancies, tick tock, just pick a mood

19
00:01:20,440 --> 00:01:22,010
A drizzle from a patch of blue sky

20
00:01:23,040 --> 00:01:25,310
No less than supreme

21
00:01:25,310 --> 00:01:28,720
A maiden's heart zigzags, cute and invincible

22
00:01:29,610 --> 00:01:31,330
The wild ringing of bells

23
00:01:32,360 --> 00:01:38,440
What percentage does "like" have to hit before you can call it "love"?

24
00:01:39,200 --> 00:01:42,120
Hold me so tightly that I fall asleep

25
00:01:44,160 --> 00:01:47,670
A daydream that seems like fiction

26
00:01:47,670 --> 00:01:50,710
Give me a kiss that breaks the expectant silence of the play

27
00:01:50,710 --> 00:01:53,130
Give that indecision a tight embrace, too

28
00:01:53,440 --> 00:01:55,750
My heart hurts and hurts,

29
00:01:55,750 --> 00:02:00,640
racing unpredictably with joy and excitement

30
00:02:00,640 --> 00:02:04,120
It's TRUE LOVE! Hold me tight!

31
00:02:04,120 --> 00:02:06,440
Be brave, my darling

32
00:02:06,440 --> 00:02:09,020
It won't all be happy and fun

33
00:02:09,020 --> 00:02:11,040
It's all up to us

34
00:02:11,040 --> 00:02:13,230
ONCE MORE SMILE, TWICE MORE CHIME

35
00:02:13,230 --> 00:02:16,900
Please look my way, darling

36
00:02:17,920 --> 00:02:26,000
Please notice my pure love for you

37
00:02:32,210 --> 00:02:35,040
Steve? Where are you?

38
00:02:35,640 --> 00:02:36,260
Come on.

39
00:02:37,900 --> 00:02:39,400
Steve?

40
00:02:43,230 --> 00:02:44,420
Steve?

41
00:02:46,130 --> 00:02:47,520
Are you in there?

42
00:02:47,840 --> 00:02:48,910
Are you all right?

43
00:02:53,330 --> 00:02:56,290
Is there really any reason to watch horror movies so late at night?

44
00:02:56,980 --> 00:02:59,240
It's so we can reach A-rank.

45
00:02:59,240 --> 00:03:00,150
Huh?

46
00:03:00,150 --> 00:03:02,240
Natsumi told me that

47
00:03:02,240 --> 00:03:05,700
if you watch horror movies together, you can get a lot of points!

48
00:03:06,640 --> 00:03:09,070
Huh? Why'd you turn it off?

49
00:03:09,070 --> 00:03:12,170
I just... don't think the horror plan is gonna work.

50
00:03:12,170 --> 00:03:13,680
Stop it!

51
00:03:13,680 --> 00:03:15,100
"Stop it"?

52
00:03:15,100 --> 00:03:18,170
We're gonna overcome the fear together and earn some points!

53
00:03:18,670 --> 00:03:22,090
And then we're gonna achieve A-rank and swap partners!

54
00:03:22,090 --> 00:03:24,180
You want to be paired with Sakurazaka-san, don't you?

55
00:03:24,910 --> 00:03:26,890
Well, yeah, if it's possible.

56
00:03:26,890 --> 00:03:29,350
Then to make the plan more effective...

57
00:03:29,350 --> 00:03:30,680
Wear this!

58
00:03:32,160 --> 00:03:33,900
I bought these at a sale!

59
00:03:34,680 --> 00:03:35,920
Twinsies pajamas!

60
00:03:35,920 --> 00:03:37,200
No way! I can't!

61
00:03:37,200 --> 00:03:38,840
What? Why?

62
00:03:38,840 --> 00:03:39,940
You have to ask?!

63
00:03:39,940 --> 00:03:41,930
It's something married couples would do, right?

64
00:03:41,930 --> 00:03:44,440
Apparently, we can earn points just by wearing them.

65
00:03:44,440 --> 00:03:47,360
And look! If you put them side-by-side, it makes a heart!

66
00:03:47,360 --> 00:03:49,710
I'm amazed you were able to buy a design like that.

67
00:03:49,710 --> 00:03:52,460
Going overboard in every way is exactly what we need to do.

68
00:03:53,840 --> 00:03:55,320
Come on. Hurry up and put it on.

69
00:03:55,320 --> 00:03:56,610
Really?

70
00:03:57,680 --> 00:04:00,210
She used her own money for something like this?

71
00:04:00,720 --> 00:04:01,820
I don't get it.

72
00:04:01,820 --> 00:04:04,880
She's been all fired up since the day she went to karaoke with Tenjin.

73
00:04:06,210 --> 00:04:09,480
Something must have happened between them that night.

74
00:04:10,220 --> 00:04:12,080
I mean, not that it matters!

75
00:04:12,080 --> 00:04:14,480
Why am I acting like it bothers me?

76
00:04:16,440 --> 00:04:18,450
Wh-What is it?

77
00:04:18,450 --> 00:04:21,550
Face the other way. I'm going to change.

78
00:04:21,550 --> 00:04:22,360
What?

79
00:04:22,360 --> 00:04:23,610
Here?!

80
00:04:24,520 --> 00:04:25,830
I'm changing now.

81
00:04:28,120 --> 00:04:30,500
Damn it. That's a gyaru for you.

82
00:04:30,500 --> 00:04:33,770
No need to hesitate since she has so much experience, I guess?

83
00:04:33,770 --> 00:04:36,630
Well, if she's gonna be that way, then fine. I'll put it on.

84
00:04:36,630 --> 00:04:40,000
She probably doesn't even count me as a man, anyway.

85
00:04:46,120 --> 00:04:47,170
A blackout?

86
00:04:47,170 --> 00:04:48,690
I can't see anything.

87
00:04:48,690 --> 00:04:51,390
Hey, Watanabe! Are you...

88
00:04:51,880 --> 00:04:52,700
okay?

89
00:04:55,640 --> 00:04:57,270
What?!

90
00:04:57,270 --> 00:04:59,090
Is this even possible?

91
00:04:59,090 --> 00:05:02,230
Hang on. What is this... softness... pressing up... against my chest...

92
00:05:02,230 --> 00:05:04,030
Huh? What... part of her... is that?

93
00:05:04,030 --> 00:05:05,240
Wait, this is bad!

94
00:05:05,240 --> 00:05:08,280
If I don't move my hips back, my zombie will...

95
00:05:09,030 --> 00:05:11,500
Don't beep at me right now, damn it!

96
00:05:13,440 --> 00:05:14,510
Watanabe?

97
00:05:15,990 --> 00:05:18,410
She's so scared, and I'm just...

98
00:05:19,140 --> 00:05:21,320
Sorry. I'll get my cell phone light and—

99
00:05:21,320 --> 00:05:21,800
Wait!

100
00:05:21,800 --> 00:05:22,920
Not now!

101
00:05:28,240 --> 00:05:30,810
Jerk! Don't look at me when I'm crying, you perv!

102
00:05:30,810 --> 00:05:32,960
Yeah, I'm scared! Got a problem with that?!

103
00:05:32,960 --> 00:05:34,550
Stupid! Stupid! Stupid!

104
00:05:34,550 --> 00:05:36,060
C-Calm down! I didn't see it!

105
00:05:36,060 --> 00:05:38,980
I barely saw your face at all!

106
00:05:42,490 --> 00:05:43,480
It's not working.

107
00:05:44,200 --> 00:05:46,970
We can't get into our rooms until the power comes back on.

108
00:05:48,130 --> 00:05:49,200
Hey...

109
00:05:49,700 --> 00:05:53,050
If you can't fix it, then hurry up and get back over here.

110
00:05:53,050 --> 00:05:54,590
Yeah, fine.

111
00:05:56,080 --> 00:05:58,940
She's so scared, and yet she's still bossing me around.

112
00:05:59,710 --> 00:06:02,380
She really doesn't think much of me at all.

113
00:06:04,080 --> 00:06:04,880
Though...

114
00:06:04,880 --> 00:06:07,960
Seeing Watanabe like this is super rare, so I guess it's fine.

115
00:06:08,390 --> 00:06:09,390
Also...

116
00:06:09,390 --> 00:06:11,200
Why is she pressed up against me?!

117
00:06:11,200 --> 00:06:13,070
Hey, say something fun.

118
00:06:13,070 --> 00:06:15,640
Here come the unreasonable demands of a party girl!

119
00:06:16,240 --> 00:06:18,210
Come on, don't you have anything?

120
00:06:18,210 --> 00:06:22,040
If you can't tell a fun story or two, girls will never like you.

121
00:06:22,880 --> 00:06:24,150
This little...

122
00:06:24,150 --> 00:06:27,380
Come on. What's wrong, Killjoy-kun?

123
00:06:27,940 --> 00:06:30,400
Long, long ago, in a far-off land...

124
00:06:30,400 --> 00:06:33,000
Seriously? A fairy tale?

125
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:37,660
There was an old well that even the elderly couple living nearby

126
00:06:37,660 --> 00:06:40,670
would never, ever go near.

127
00:06:41,700 --> 00:06:42,420
Hang on...

128
00:06:42,420 --> 00:06:45,700
There was a legend about that old well.

129
00:06:46,220 --> 00:06:49,600
On stormy nights, when thunder and lightning crash...

130
00:06:49,600 --> 00:06:52,700
There, beside the well, where no one should be,

131
00:06:52,700 --> 00:06:55,420
stands the ghost of a woman with long hair...

132
00:06:56,680 --> 00:07:00,050
Huh? Watanabe-san? Um...

133
00:07:00,050 --> 00:07:02,140
Why'd you go all quiet?

134
00:07:02,140 --> 00:07:05,500
Are you going to suddenly jump at me and scream to freak me out?

135
00:07:05,500 --> 00:07:08,480
Wait, you didn't think that was actually scary, did you?

136
00:07:08,480 --> 00:07:10,990
Vermin. Virgin. Go die and let the worms in.

137
00:07:10,990 --> 00:07:13,060
Her insults rhyme like she's rapping!

138
00:07:14,120 --> 00:07:15,670
Sorry.

139
00:07:15,670 --> 00:07:18,970
Seeing you scared was just so unexpected, I couldn't help it.

140
00:07:19,460 --> 00:07:23,540
Minami-kun wouldn't have done that. He'd have been nice to me.

141
00:07:23,820 --> 00:07:25,750
I really am sorry.

142
00:07:26,250 --> 00:07:27,550
But you know...

143
00:07:27,550 --> 00:07:31,110
There's no one else here right now but you.

144
00:07:33,210 --> 00:07:36,860
Would it kill you to let me depend on you a little? Meanie.

145
00:07:37,560 --> 00:07:38,560
She's so cu—

146
00:07:41,310 --> 00:07:42,930
That was close!

147
00:07:42,930 --> 00:07:45,020
What was that?! What is she after?

148
00:07:45,020 --> 00:07:47,320
Is she just messing with a virgin?!

149
00:07:48,650 --> 00:07:50,620
My face is on fire!

150
00:07:50,620 --> 00:07:52,070
It's gotta be bright red right now!

151
00:07:52,070 --> 00:07:54,040
I'm so glad it's dark.

152
00:07:54,040 --> 00:07:55,280
Oh! I found it!

153
00:07:55,950 --> 00:07:58,460
It's a flameless aromatherapy candle.

154
00:07:58,460 --> 00:07:59,500
Huh?

155
00:07:59,500 --> 00:08:01,960
Natsumi gave it to me today.

156
00:08:03,700 --> 00:08:05,930
For our two-year anniversary of hanging out together!

157
00:08:05,930 --> 00:08:08,180
It came in a set of three, so it was a bargain!

158
00:08:13,560 --> 00:08:15,980
Oh, wow! It smells super nice!

159
00:08:15,980 --> 00:08:17,920
Ugh, it's so sweet.

160
00:08:17,920 --> 00:08:20,660
I guess guys don't understand stuff like this.

161
00:08:32,880 --> 00:08:34,100
Watanabe.

162
00:08:35,890 --> 00:08:36,660
Yeah?

163
00:08:43,210 --> 00:08:44,460
You're cute.

164
00:08:49,550 --> 00:08:51,630
What did I just say?

165
00:08:52,330 --> 00:08:54,310
I've lost my mind!

166
00:08:54,310 --> 00:08:56,640
Did she hear me? She heard me, didn't she?

167
00:08:57,210 --> 00:08:59,440
She's asleep! I'm safe!

168
00:09:00,540 --> 00:09:03,890
Seriously, though, she looks so cute when she's asleep.

169
00:09:04,730 --> 00:09:07,140
She tried to watch a horror movie, even though she doesn't like them.

170
00:09:07,140 --> 00:09:09,060
Pushing herself so hard must've worn her out.

171
00:09:10,560 --> 00:09:13,150
Would it kill you to let me depend on you a little?

172
00:09:15,710 --> 00:09:18,160
What does it mean to let someone depend on you?

173
00:09:18,570 --> 00:09:21,290
What's it mean to be a married couple?

174
00:09:21,760 --> 00:09:24,490
Goodnight, Watanabe.

175
00:09:32,060 --> 00:09:34,900
Stupid. What was all that supposed to mean?

176
00:09:39,300 --> 00:09:39,900
Huh?

177
00:09:39,900 --> 00:09:41,810
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey!

178
00:09:41,810 --> 00:09:45,310
11th Ogoori Yutaka Kamachi Izumi 12th Yakuin Jiro Watanabe Akari 13th Okubo Osamu Shuto Kyoko You've done pretty well there, my friend.

179
00:09:45,810 --> 00:09:48,140
To think that innocent little boy, Jiro-chan,

180
00:09:48,140 --> 00:09:52,370
and a gyaru of the highest rank are living as a B-ranked married couple.

181
00:09:53,050 --> 00:09:55,320
Your mama is so happy she's gonna cry.

182
00:09:56,430 --> 00:09:58,820
And what about you?

183
00:09:58,820 --> 00:10:00,700
Kasugahara Kyo Sangamori Hatsune Kamo Sadaharu Kaneyama Satsuki Shingu Aoba I'm C-ranked this time, but it's not a problem.

184
00:10:01,410 --> 00:10:03,990
I'm aiming for A-rank next time!

185
00:10:03,990 --> 00:10:05,240
When you switch partners,

186
00:10:05,240 --> 00:10:08,920
the points for the two of you can be combined. It's a major bargain!

187
00:10:08,920 --> 00:10:09,830
Whoa... Watanabe...

188
00:10:10,740 --> 00:10:11,540
No way.

189
00:10:12,330 --> 00:10:13,900
E-rank?

190
00:10:13,900 --> 00:10:14,460
Huh?

191
00:10:16,470 --> 00:10:18,970
71st Shirono Honami 71st Tenjin Minami Sakurazaka Shiori 71st Kaizuka Yoshitake Nakahara Miyako

192
00:10:21,920 --> 00:10:23,470
After that...

193
00:10:24,280 --> 00:10:27,420
I couldn't stop worrying about Shiori.

194
00:10:28,340 --> 00:10:31,480
But it wasn't like I could ask her anything directly.

195
00:10:31,980 --> 00:10:33,860
All I could do was vaguely wonder.

196
00:10:34,670 --> 00:10:38,200
It made me a little happy that things weren't working out with Tenjin,

197
00:10:40,070 --> 00:10:42,800
but no matter how well we acted like the perfect married couple,

198
00:10:42,800 --> 00:10:44,710
or how many points we earned...

199
00:10:44,710 --> 00:10:47,870
If Shiori and Tenjin weren't A-ranked, none of it mattered.

200
00:10:51,120 --> 00:10:53,130
Music Room

201
00:11:03,510 --> 00:11:05,940
You're really amazing, Mei-chan.

202
00:11:05,940 --> 00:11:08,140
You're good at sports, and you can play piano, too.

203
00:11:08,830 --> 00:11:11,640
I just played it some a long time ago, that's all.

204
00:11:11,640 --> 00:11:14,900
More importantly, are you feeling a little better?

205
00:11:15,670 --> 00:11:17,900
I thought you might have noticed.

206
00:11:18,170 --> 00:11:19,840
Which reason is it?

207
00:11:19,840 --> 00:11:21,990
That he's out with a cold?

208
00:11:21,990 --> 00:11:24,500
Or is it about your married life?

209
00:11:24,500 --> 00:11:25,590
Well...

210
00:11:25,590 --> 00:11:26,910
Both, huh?

211
00:11:27,600 --> 00:11:31,720
When it comes to my married life, I already know...

212
00:11:31,720 --> 00:11:35,730
that it's my own fault because I'm not good with people I don't know.

213
00:11:38,360 --> 00:11:40,450
Ugh, this is such a drag.

214
00:11:44,800 --> 00:11:47,810
Watanabe Akari Forgot my key. Let me in when I ring the intercom. Don't keep me waiting

215
00:11:46,420 --> 00:11:47,810
All right, all right.

216
00:11:48,250 --> 00:11:50,310
I'm sick here, you know...

217
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:53,480
I'm gonna hang out with my friends today.

218
00:11:53,900 --> 00:11:57,480
Watanabe Akari Forgot my key. Let me in when I ring the intercom. Don't keep me waiting You got it Shouldn't we be using a day like this to rack up points?

219
00:11:58,400 --> 00:12:01,990
If it were Shiori, would she be kind and look after me?

220
00:12:06,120 --> 00:12:07,710
Say "ah."

221
00:12:09,270 --> 00:12:11,450
What am I, a middle-schooler?!

222
00:12:12,480 --> 00:12:14,480
It's not for real, but we are married.

223
00:12:14,480 --> 00:12:19,250
You could come home early for me, couldn't you, Watanabe?

224
00:12:20,880 --> 00:12:23,030
Huh? For real?

225
00:12:24,600 --> 00:12:26,960
No. No, no way.

226
00:12:27,390 --> 00:12:30,020
Why does this make me feel a little bit happy?

227
00:12:31,520 --> 00:12:33,520
Y-You're back early, Watanabe...

228
00:12:33,800 --> 00:12:36,070
Oh, good! You're awake!

229
00:12:36,880 --> 00:12:38,440
How's your cold?

230
00:12:41,320 --> 00:12:41,900
Shio—

231
00:12:42,720 --> 00:12:44,120
Sakurazaka?

232
00:12:45,320 --> 00:12:46,960
Thank you for waiting.

233
00:12:46,960 --> 00:12:48,530
The pancakes are here!

234
00:12:48,530 --> 00:12:49,790
They look tasty!

235
00:12:49,790 --> 00:12:51,750
I guess we should dig in.

236
00:12:52,490 --> 00:12:54,410
What's wrong, Akari?

237
00:12:54,410 --> 00:12:57,120
You're the one who said you wanted these.

238
00:12:57,120 --> 00:12:59,310
Huh? Oh... Yeah!

239
00:12:59,310 --> 00:13:00,300
They look delicious.

240
00:13:00,860 --> 00:13:04,070
I bet you were thinking about Minami-kun, right?

241
00:13:04,070 --> 00:13:04,530
Huh?

242
00:13:04,530 --> 00:13:08,400
That's pretty much the only thing Akari thinks about so seriously.

243
00:13:08,400 --> 00:13:10,560
Forget about that! Let's just eat, okay?

244
00:13:10,910 --> 00:13:12,620
Let's eat!

245
00:13:13,280 --> 00:13:18,880
Hey, did you know? Apparently, these pancakes are called "a prince's kiss."

246
00:13:18,880 --> 00:13:20,780
What? That's hilarious.

247
00:13:20,780 --> 00:13:24,070
The texture of the edge is supposed to be as soft as someone's lips.

248
00:13:27,560 --> 00:13:30,080
No, no, no! It's not like that at all!

249
00:13:30,800 --> 00:13:34,550
Akari? Why are you so dead-set on denying it?

250
00:13:34,550 --> 00:13:38,000
Wait, don't tell me that after that night at karaoke...

251
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:40,330
You and Minami-kun went and did it?

252
00:13:40,330 --> 00:13:42,440
O-Of course not.

253
00:13:44,990 --> 00:13:48,090
Ugh... Why am I even thinking about him?

254
00:13:48,900 --> 00:13:52,600
I was surprised, is all. I never expected you to come over.

255
00:13:52,950 --> 00:13:55,850
Thanks for buying all this stuff for me.

256
00:13:56,090 --> 00:13:58,740
No, it was Watanabe-san, actually.

257
00:13:58,740 --> 00:14:02,570
She said, "I have stuff to do, so would you look after Jiro-kun?"

258
00:14:02,570 --> 00:14:05,110
And I was worried, too, so here I am.

259
00:14:05,430 --> 00:14:06,860
Watanabe said that?

260
00:14:06,860 --> 00:14:09,320
Yeah. Should we replace your forehead compress?

261
00:14:09,740 --> 00:14:11,580
Thank you, Watanabe!

262
00:14:11,580 --> 00:14:15,120
Shiori really came to my room!

263
00:14:15,770 --> 00:14:18,540
Do you remember back when we were in elementary school?

264
00:14:20,910 --> 00:14:22,250
When I stayed home with a cold,

265
00:14:23,060 --> 00:14:25,500
you brought me our class handouts.

266
00:14:26,260 --> 00:14:28,880
You changed the cold compress on my forehead.

267
00:14:29,600 --> 00:14:31,300
It made me so happy!

268
00:14:33,210 --> 00:14:35,140
I-Is that what happened?

269
00:14:35,140 --> 00:14:36,970
All right, I'll put it on.

270
00:14:36,970 --> 00:14:38,310
Give me your forehead.

271
00:14:39,020 --> 00:14:41,010
Uh, s-sure.

272
00:14:42,840 --> 00:14:44,540
Don't move, now.

273
00:14:45,710 --> 00:14:49,000
Sh-Sh-She's so cute!

274
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:50,380
There. All done.

275
00:14:50,380 --> 00:14:52,170
Th-Thanks.

276
00:14:52,170 --> 00:14:53,410
No problem.

277
00:14:53,410 --> 00:14:55,960
I'm glad to see you're doing better than I thought.

278
00:14:56,560 --> 00:14:58,180
I'm going to borrow your kitchen, okay?

279
00:14:58,180 --> 00:14:59,410
Sure.

280
00:15:09,180 --> 00:15:10,950
If she does stuff like this for me...

281
00:15:12,450 --> 00:15:14,640
I'm gonna get the wrong idea again.

282
00:15:15,120 --> 00:15:16,640
Just like I did back then.

283
00:15:17,950 --> 00:15:19,840
In the summer of our second year of middle school,

284
00:15:19,840 --> 00:15:23,140
when Shiori had to change schools because her dad got transferred at work,

285
00:15:23,810 --> 00:15:26,420
I had intended to confess my feelings to her.

286
00:15:27,080 --> 00:15:30,420
Oh, so you're transferring to a private school.

287
00:15:30,420 --> 00:15:31,110
Yeah.

288
00:15:31,700 --> 00:15:33,180
Shiori, I—

289
00:15:33,180 --> 00:15:34,200
Say, Jiro-kun...

290
00:15:34,660 --> 00:15:36,240
Even if we're apart...

291
00:15:37,520 --> 00:15:39,830
Will you always stay my friend?

292
00:15:43,760 --> 00:15:45,590
Yeah. I will.

293
00:15:47,690 --> 00:15:49,480
Nothing's gonna change.

294
00:15:50,580 --> 00:15:54,200
I suddenly got scared, so I chickened out on confessing to her,

295
00:15:55,160 --> 00:15:57,350
but I think it was for the best in the end.

296
00:15:58,140 --> 00:15:59,340
Jiro-kun?

297
00:16:01,920 --> 00:16:04,600
Huh? Oh, sorry! I zoned out...

298
00:16:04,860 --> 00:16:07,460
I made some rice porridge. Do you think you can eat?

299
00:16:07,460 --> 00:16:08,220
For real? Yeah.

300
00:16:08,860 --> 00:16:11,180
Yes! I'll eat it! I'll eat it with tremendous gratitude!

301
00:16:12,210 --> 00:16:14,750
Oh, man! Shiori's cooking!

302
00:16:14,750 --> 00:16:17,370
This is the best thing I've ever tasted in my whole life!

303
00:16:17,370 --> 00:16:20,550
I'm so glad. It looks like you're able to eat on your own.

304
00:16:20,550 --> 00:16:21,450
Huh? Uh...

305
00:16:22,710 --> 00:16:24,330
Say "ah"!

306
00:16:25,510 --> 00:16:30,140
Oh, crap! If I hadn't dug right in, I'd have had the chance for her to feed me.

307
00:16:30,140 --> 00:16:31,220
Are you all right?

308
00:16:31,220 --> 00:16:32,450
I-It's nothing.

309
00:16:34,060 --> 00:16:36,080
It's so delicious, it's making me cry.

310
00:16:36,080 --> 00:16:38,100
Oh, I'm so glad!

311
00:16:39,490 --> 00:16:40,700
Thanks for the porridge.

312
00:16:40,700 --> 00:16:42,100
I'm glad you liked it.

313
00:16:43,360 --> 00:16:45,100
Must be nice to be Tenjin.

314
00:16:45,640 --> 00:16:48,430
He gets to eat your cooking every day.

315
00:16:48,430 --> 00:16:50,650
We take turns doing the cooking.

316
00:16:50,650 --> 00:16:52,480
We rotate every day.

317
00:16:52,480 --> 00:16:56,170
R-Really? Wow, Tenjin can cook, too?

318
00:16:56,170 --> 00:16:58,870
No wonder Watanabe's always squeeing over him.

319
00:16:58,870 --> 00:17:01,710
My cooking is truly catastrophic,

320
00:17:01,710 --> 00:17:04,180
so I just leave it all to Watanabe.

321
00:17:04,180 --> 00:17:06,480
Despite how she looks, she's really good at it.

322
00:17:06,480 --> 00:17:07,640
Unexpected, right?

323
00:17:07,640 --> 00:17:11,290
I mean, I do the other housework to make up for it, though.

324
00:17:11,850 --> 00:17:13,440
That's right.

325
00:17:13,440 --> 00:17:16,380
Everything's going well between you and her, huh?

326
00:17:17,440 --> 00:17:19,870
Hey, um, Sakurazaka...

327
00:17:20,320 --> 00:17:22,360
I saw your ranking...

328
00:17:22,940 --> 00:17:25,530
and if there's anything I can do, just say it.

329
00:17:25,530 --> 00:17:27,770
I'll help you.

330
00:17:28,710 --> 00:17:30,270
Sorry, Shiori.

331
00:17:30,590 --> 00:17:35,150
I'm pretending to be a nice guy, when really, this is all for my own sake.

332
00:17:35,520 --> 00:17:37,660
Because I want to live with you.

333
00:17:38,560 --> 00:17:40,030
Thank you, Jiro-kun.

334
00:17:40,740 --> 00:17:43,410
I don't feel comfortable around boys...

335
00:17:43,810 --> 00:17:46,070
I am trying,

336
00:17:46,070 --> 00:17:49,480
but when I think about being "married," I can't help getting anxious,

337
00:17:49,480 --> 00:17:51,170
and I put distance between us.

338
00:17:51,700 --> 00:17:52,670
I see.

339
00:17:52,970 --> 00:17:56,930
I also think it might have been better if you were my husband.

340
00:17:59,960 --> 00:18:01,360
Just kidding!

341
00:18:01,360 --> 00:18:04,710
Watanabe-san will be coming home soon, won't she?

342
00:18:04,710 --> 00:18:06,180
I'll go wash the dishes.

343
00:18:06,180 --> 00:18:07,440
It's okay!

344
00:18:07,790 --> 00:18:09,920
I-I know you can do it!

345
00:18:09,920 --> 00:18:11,750
You can do it, Shiori!

346
00:18:12,320 --> 00:18:16,120
I've been your friend since we were little, so I can vouch for all your good points!

347
00:18:16,120 --> 00:18:17,320
So have confidence in yourself!

348
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:19,710
Th-Thank—

349
00:18:19,710 --> 00:18:21,320
Sorry!

350
00:18:21,320 --> 00:18:23,590
Crap! She was totally weirded out by that!

351
00:18:23,590 --> 00:18:26,360
Shiori was really, really weirded out by that!

352
00:18:26,360 --> 00:18:29,820
Don't get all excited and lunge at her, you virgin!

353
00:18:29,820 --> 00:18:32,090
Oh, I just want to die now.

354
00:18:38,080 --> 00:18:38,840
And anyway...

355
00:18:39,400 --> 00:18:43,350
Shiori only came here because Watanabe asked her to.

356
00:18:44,120 --> 00:18:47,370
And once she gets used to Tenjin, things'll work out between them.

357
00:18:47,370 --> 00:18:50,760
Once Shiori stops being against the idea, I'm sure...

358
00:18:54,500 --> 00:18:55,720
Jiro-kun.

359
00:18:55,720 --> 00:18:57,110
Are you asleep?

360
00:18:57,980 --> 00:19:00,360
You finally called me by my first name like I asked.

361
00:19:00,760 --> 00:19:03,370
I was so happy my mind went blank.

362
00:19:04,080 --> 00:19:06,000
Say, Jiro-kun...

363
00:19:08,820 --> 00:19:09,820
I...

364
00:19:14,640 --> 00:19:19,260
So did you hear the rumor that Sakurazaka-san is avoiding Minami-kun?

365
00:19:20,660 --> 00:19:23,520
I hear she's popular 'cause she's the pure, sweet type.

366
00:19:23,520 --> 00:19:26,200
And it seems like she's not comfortable talking to guys.

367
00:19:26,200 --> 00:19:29,600
But Akarin and Killjoy-kun seem to be getting along pretty well, right?

368
00:19:29,600 --> 00:19:31,270
Maybe they've already done it.

369
00:19:31,270 --> 00:19:34,900
No way. Virgin-kun could never go that far.

370
00:19:35,190 --> 00:19:37,590
I'm more worried about Minami-kun.

371
00:19:37,590 --> 00:19:40,560
She won't go near him now, but it'll be dangerous once she's used to him.

372
00:19:40,560 --> 00:19:42,510
Sakurazaka-san's cute, after all.

373
00:19:42,510 --> 00:19:44,540
If she makes a move with that face...

374
00:19:44,540 --> 00:19:45,420
Oh...

375
00:19:45,420 --> 00:19:46,990
What're you gonna do, Akari?

376
00:19:46,990 --> 00:19:49,650
Your husband's gonna get taken away.

377
00:19:49,650 --> 00:19:50,440
Yeah.

378
00:19:52,160 --> 00:19:53,420
Maybe.

379
00:19:59,240 --> 00:20:01,930
I shouldn't... right?

380
00:20:02,180 --> 00:20:03,930
We aren't married, so how could I?

381
00:20:05,110 --> 00:20:07,700
Will you always stay my friend?

382
00:20:09,960 --> 00:20:11,180
Yeah. I will.

383
00:20:12,610 --> 00:20:14,440
Nothing's gonna change.

384
00:20:15,100 --> 00:20:17,020
Oh, I'm so relieved!

385
00:20:17,800 --> 00:20:21,230
The place we're moving to isn't that far away,

386
00:20:21,230 --> 00:20:24,000
and I want to come back here sometimes.

387
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:29,490
You know how the Christmas lights around the train station are really pretty?

388
00:20:29,490 --> 00:20:32,710
So I was thinking I'd like to see them again this year.

389
00:20:32,710 --> 00:20:37,000
And, um... if you wouldn't mind, Jiro-kun...

390
00:20:37,000 --> 00:20:37,960
Shiori...

391
00:20:37,960 --> 00:20:41,460
Sorry. I just remembered something I have to do, so I'm gonna go.

392
00:20:42,560 --> 00:20:43,300
Sure.

393
00:20:44,460 --> 00:20:45,530
I'll see you later.

394
00:20:46,020 --> 00:20:49,480
Back then, I thought "later" would never come.

395
00:20:51,460 --> 00:20:52,250
But...

396
00:20:53,330 --> 00:20:55,390
If I tried my hardest again,

397
00:20:55,390 --> 00:20:58,730
would he hear me out to the end this time?

398
00:21:03,960 --> 00:21:05,240
I'm back.

399
00:21:09,700 --> 00:21:11,240
What're you gonna do, Akari?

400
00:21:11,240 --> 00:21:14,000
Your husband's gonna get taken away.

401
00:21:17,530 --> 00:21:18,220
Okay! Watanabe?

402
00:21:19,150 --> 00:21:20,970
Where'd you come from?!

403
00:21:20,970 --> 00:21:22,110
You scared me!

404
00:21:22,110 --> 00:21:26,180
S-Sorry. Um, I just wanted to talk for a minute.

405
00:21:26,180 --> 00:21:29,520
What do you mean? Are you feeling better already?

406
00:21:29,520 --> 00:21:31,890
Uh, yeah. Thanks to you.

407
00:21:32,880 --> 00:21:37,400
Shiori—um, Sakurazaka came over because you asked her to, right?

408
00:21:39,420 --> 00:21:43,500
I just thought that Virgin-kun would need someone to play mama for him.

409
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:44,920
I'm...

410
00:21:45,940 --> 00:21:47,910
gonna do my best to be your husband, Watanabe.

411
00:21:47,910 --> 00:21:48,710
Huh?

412
00:21:49,470 --> 00:21:53,500
I'll do even more to help you out so that things work out between you and Tenjin.

413
00:21:54,980 --> 00:21:58,570
For now, even though it was super brief, I got to live a nice dream.

414
00:21:58,570 --> 00:21:59,670
Thanks.

415
00:22:00,940 --> 00:22:03,620
I'll be going to school tomorrow, so I'm going to bed now.

416
00:22:03,620 --> 00:22:04,540
Goodnight.

417
00:22:08,500 --> 00:22:10,960
Well, that's great, right?

418
00:22:12,920 --> 00:22:13,680
So...

419
00:22:14,640 --> 00:22:18,140
why do I feel so annoyed about it?

420
00:22:19,940 --> 00:22:23,920
In this moment when I've deceived you on a cosmic scale

421
00:22:23,920 --> 00:22:28,350
I want to give love a try

422
00:22:28,350 --> 00:22:31,260
In this night when everything begins to overflow

423
00:22:31,260 --> 00:22:33,530
I match my stride to yours

424
00:22:33,530 --> 00:22:39,370
The clock hands stop, charmed by a fleeting curse

425
00:22:39,370 --> 00:22:43,940
The answers always slip away

426
00:22:43,940 --> 00:22:47,360
All I want is to do it over again

427
00:22:47,360 --> 00:22:52,760
If I did, would this unsettling gloom inside me disappear?

428
00:22:52,760 --> 00:22:57,060
I want to know where my heart is hiding

429
00:22:57,060 --> 00:23:01,840
One day this will end

430
00:23:01,840 --> 00:23:04,640
I know that

431
00:23:04,640 --> 00:23:06,350
And I know the signs of discord

432
00:23:06,350 --> 00:23:08,400
Turn them inside out

433
00:23:08,400 --> 00:23:10,000
Don't let them pile up

434
00:23:10,000 --> 00:23:14,210
I don't want things to stay unfinished like this

435
00:23:14,210 --> 00:23:18,250
In this moment when I've deceived you on a cosmic scale

436
00:23:18,250 --> 00:23:22,680
I want to give love a try

437
00:23:22,680 --> 00:23:24,700
Everything begins to overflow

438
00:23:24,700 --> 00:23:27,890
On this day when we don't know how much time is left to us

439
00:23:27,890 --> 00:23:36,150
I want your thoughts to drift toward me fondly, again and again

440
00:23:50,400 --> 00:23:52,610
Sakurazaka Shiori is a pain in the neck.

441
00:23:53,450 --> 00:23:55,850
All she does is fret over Yakuin.

442
00:23:55,850 --> 00:23:57,870
Why would she ask me anything? I don't care.

443
00:23:58,860 --> 00:24:01,750
But when our conversation was done, her reenergized expression

444
00:24:02,320 --> 00:24:04,000
was really cute.

445
00:24:04,440 --> 00:24:06,500
So I guess it's all good.

446
00:24:06,500 --> 00:24:10,010
Next Time Broken Up, and Not Rekindled.

447
00:24:06,890 --> 00:24:07,760
Next time,

448
00:24:07,760 --> 00:24:10,010
"Broken Up, and Not Rekindled."

